  "prompt": "Which coaching institute is better for cat TIME or IMS?",
  "response": "Choosing between TIME and IMS for CAT preparation depends on various factors such as faculty quality, study material, location, batch size, and individual learning preferences. Here are some points to consider for each:\n\n1. **TIME (Triumphant Institute of Management Education)**:\n   - **Established Reputation**: TIME has a longstanding reputation in CAT coaching with numerous successful alumni.\n   - **Faculty**: Generally experienced and knowledgeable.\n   - **Study Material**: Comprehensive and regularly updated.\n   - **Mock Tests**: TIME's AIMCATs are highly regarded and provide a good benchmarking against peers.\n\n2. **IMS**:\n   - **Personalized Coaching**: Often praised for its student-centric approach.\n   - **Faculty**: Competent and approachable.\n   - **Study Material**: High-quality and relevant.\n   - **Mock Tests**: SIMCATs are good for practice and analysis.\n\nFactors to assess:\n- **Proximity**: Which institute is closer and more accessible?\n- **Batch Size**: Preference for smaller batches for personalized attention or larger batches for competitiveness?\n- **Learning Style**: Do you prefer a structured approach or a more flexible learning environment?\n\nUltimately, both TIME and IMS have their strengths. Research about specific branch reviews, talk to past students, and perhaps attend demo classes to see which fits your style and needs best.",
